<DOC><DOCNO>  ZF109-701-601  </DOCNO><DOCID>09 701 601.andO;</DOCID><JOURNAL>Electronic Engineering Times  Dec 10 1990 n620 p64(1).andM;</JOURNAL><TITLE>Reliability tool bows. (Valid Logic Systems' Viablereliability-analysis tool) (product announcement)</TITLE><AUTHOR>Goering, Richard.andM;</AUTHOR><TEXT><ABSTRACT>Valid Logic Systems introduces Viable, a new reliability-analysistool that differs from most existing packages in its support foruser-defined equations.andP;  Viable is based on MIL-HDBK-217Ecalculations and can use but does not require the Allegro pc-boardlayout package and thermal analysis.andP;  In addition to boards,Viable can also model anything from integrated circuits tocomplete systems.andP;  Viable calculates mean time between failures,providing relative and absolute failure rates; results can bedisplayed in a graphical bar chart, or a report can be generatedthat describes all contributors to relative and absolute failurerates.andP;  Valid also introduces CALS-Out, a documentation packagethe conforms to the International Graphics Exchange Specificationformat and allows users to select a template at the beginning ofthe design process that will ensure that all drawings producedconform to a single drawing standard.andP;  Both packages will beavailable in Jan 1991; they run as shared software on Sun, DEC andIBM platforms.andP;  Viable is priced at $12,000; CALS-Out will sellfor $6,000.andM;</ABSTRACT></TEXT><DESCRIPT>Company:   Valid Logic Systems Inc. (Product introduction).andO;Product:   Viable (Computer program) (Product introduction)CALS-Out (Computer program) (Product introduction).andO;Topic:     Product IntroductionSoftware PackagesReliabilityDocumentationCircuit DesignComputer-Aided DesignModeling.andM;</DESCRIPT></DOC>